<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") %>

<div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-5 mx-auto" style="max-width: 720px;">
  <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
    <h1 class="h3 fw-bold mb-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-muted small mb-4">Last updated: March 29, 2026</p>

    <p class="mb-3">
      Wanderlust (“we”, “us”) respects your privacy. This page explains what information we collect when you use our listing platform and how we use it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h6 fw-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Information we collect</h2>
    <ul class="small text-secondary ps-3 mb-3">
      <li class="mb-1"><strong>Account data:</strong> username, email, and credentials you provide when you sign up or log in.</li>
      <li class="mb-1"><strong>Listing content:</strong> titles, descriptions, prices, locations, and images you upload for listings.</li>
      <li class="mb-1"><strong>Reviews:</strong> ratings and comments you post on listings.</li>
      <li class="mb-1"><strong>Technical data:</strong> session cookies and similar data needed to keep you signed in and secure.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="h6 fw-semibold mt-4 mb-2">How we use information</h2>
    <p class="small text-secondary mb-3">
      We use this data to run the service (show listings, maps, and reviews), authenticate users, improve security, and communicate important notices about your account or the platform.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h6 fw-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Images &amp; third-party services</h2>
    <p class="small text-secondary mb-3">
      Listing images may be stored and delivered through a cloud provider (e.g. Cloudinary). Maps may be provided by a third party (e.g. Mapbox). Those services process data under their own policies.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h6 fw-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Your choices</h2>
    <p class="small text-secondary mb-3">
      You can review and update your listings while logged in. You may contact us to ask about account-related data or to report a concern.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h6 fw-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Contact</h2>
    <p class="small text-secondary mb-0">
      For privacy questions, reach us through the contact options shown on this site (or your course project maintainer).
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
